cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.EC, cs.IT, cs.MA. 

The paper deals with revenue maximization in selling two goods, which is a classic problem in game theory and economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and duality theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of exact complementarity in the proof indicates that it could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper is concerned with selling mechanisms and auctions, which falls under cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
